            <RecipeTitle>Speedy spaghetti with clams</RecipeTitle>
            
            <RecipePicture>http://dmb-team.com/assets/recipe/speedy_spaghetti.png</RecipePicture>
            
            <RecipeSummary>
                <RecipeSummaryOrigin>Italy</RecipeSummaryOrigin>
                <RecipeSummaryPreparationTime>n/a</RecipeSummaryPreparationTime>
                <RecipeSummaryCookingTime>15-20 mins</RecipeSummaryCookingTime>
                <RecipeSummaryPortions>2</RecipeSummaryPortions>
                <RecipeSummaryCalories>385</RecipeSummaryCalories>
                <RecipeSummaryDescription>This simple Italian pasta dish uses jars of clams in tomato sauce – a great time-saver</RecipeSummaryDescription>
            </RecipeSummary>
            
            <RecipeIngredientsList>
                <RecipeIngredient>
                    <RecipeIngredientsName>spaghetti</RecipeIngredientsName>
                    <RecipeIngredientsQuantity>175 g</RecipeIngredientsQuantity>
                </RecipeIngredient>
                 <RecipeIngredient>
                    <RecipeIngredientsName>jars clams in tomato sauce</RecipeIngredientsName>
                    <RecipeIngredientsQuantity>2 x 130 g</RecipeIngredientsQuantity>
                </RecipeIngredient>
                 <RecipeIngredient>
                    <RecipeIngredientsName>splash of wine, whatever you have</RecipeIngredientsName>
                    <RecipeIngredientsQuantity/>
                </RecipeIngredient>
                 <RecipeIngredient>
                    <RecipeIngredientsName>garlic clove, finely crushed</RecipeIngredientsName>
                    <RecipeIngredientsQuantity>1</RecipeIngredientsQuantity>
                </RecipeIngredient>
                 <RecipeIngredient>
                    <RecipeIngredientsName>handful parsley</RecipeIngredientsName>
                    <RecipeIngredientsQuantity>n/a</RecipeIngredientsQuantity>
                </RecipeIngredient>
                 <RecipeIngredient>
                    <RecipeIngredientsName>freshly grated parmesan, to serve (optional)</RecipeIngredientsName>
                    <RecipeIngredientsQuantity>n/a</RecipeIngredientsQuantity>
                </RecipeIngredient>
            </RecipeIngredientsList>
            
            <RecipeStepsList>
                <RecipeStep>
                    <RecipeStepName>Step 1: </RecipeStepName>
                    <RecipeStepDescription>Firstly, cook the pasta. Boil the kettle, then three-quarters fill a large pan with boiling water. Add some salt – the water will seethe – then coil in the spaghetti. Simmer, uncovered, for 12 mins or according to pack instructions.</RecipeStepDescription>
                </RecipeStep>
                <RecipeStep>
                    <RecipeStepName>Step 2: </RecipeStepName>
                    <RecipeStepDescription>Meanwhile, to make the sauce, tip the clam sauce into a small pan, pour in the wine and add the garlic. Simmer for a few mins while you coarsely chop the parsley, then stir into the sauce and grind in a good amount of black pepper.</RecipeStepDescription>
                </RecipeStep>
                <RecipeStep>
                    <RecipeStepName>Step 3: </RecipeStepName>
                    <RecipeStepDescription>Drain the spaghetti and tip into a warmed bowl. Pour in the sauce and toss well. Serve at once, with grated parmesan scattered over if you like.</RecipeStepDescription>
                </RecipeStep>
            </RecipeStepsList>
            
        </RecipeInfo>
